# Trove catalog (never skip for new/changed products)

## Pricing formula (every variant)
- `retail = ceil((cjCost + cjShip) / (1 - 0.20 - 0.034)) - 0.01`, cap `$39.99`
- `compareAt = ceil(retail * 1.1) - 0.01`
- Bundle variants (`2pcs`, `2set`, `Set4`) use **that variant's CJ cost**, not 2× unit price
- Cart qty 2 = `price × 2`; server recalculates via `validateStoreOrder` — never trust client prices
- PayPal `create-order` must pass **`variantId`** + slug + quantity

## CJ ship defaults
- pet `4`, home `4`, wellness `3.5`, tech `3.5` (override per product when CJ differs)

## Adding / relinking a product
1. Copy in `scripts/product-copy.json` for the slug
2. `node --env-file=.env.local scripts/relink-product-cj.mjs <slug> <pid> [ship]`
3. Verify with `grep` on `products.ts` (name + cjSku match listing)
4. **`npm run catalog:check`** before commit — must pass
5. Build + deploy + push

## Scripts (always use these)
| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `npm run catalog:check` | Gate: blocks, variants, duplicate cjVid/cjSku |
| `npm run catalog:check:cj` | Above + full CJ price audit (127 products) |
| `npm run catalog:duplicates` | Human-readable duplicate report |
| `node scripts/sync-all-variants.mjs` | Refresh variants (only after parser fix verified) |

## Parser safety
- Use `extractProductBlock` / `replaceProductBlock` from `scripts/lib/cj-catalog-lib.mjs` only
- Never parse products with fragile `indexOf("\n  }")` — breaks on bad indent / blank lines
- Product blocks must start with `\n  {` (2 spaces), not `    {`

## Variant UI
- Uniform grid in `product-variant-picker.tsx` — equal square thumbnails, labels below
- Show per-variant `$` when prices differ
- Mobile: 3-col variant grid, compact header (~100px), sticky Add to Cart bar on product page, `text-xl` max for product titles, `pb-20` for sticky bar clearance

## Pre-deploy checklist
```
npm run catalog:check && npm run build && npm run deploy
git push origin main
```
